<br>
Head - Rotting Gorilla Hide Helmet<br>
Neck - Dragon Tooth Choker (Sometimes swapped w/ shrouded medallion, amulet of the grey wastes)<br>
Face - Faceguard of Bentos the Hero<br>
Ears - Griffon Fang Earring, Wolf Fang Earring<br>
Chest - Fungi Tunic<br>
Back - Dire Wolfhide Cloak<br>
Arms - Azure Sleeves<br>
Shoulders - Meditative Blanket<br>
Wrists - Bracer of Benevolence, Tyn Shackle<br>
Waist - Silvery Belt of Contention<br>
Hands - Epic<br>
Fingers - 2x Velium Fire Wedding Ring<br>
Range - Goranga Idol<br>
Legs - Thurg Legs<br>
Weapons - Tranquil Staff, Epic Fists<br>
Extra: Tink Bag, Rallic Pack, the usual resist gear, HoT bracer.<br>
<br>
So I have a few questions.<br>
<br>
1) What should be my next upgrade or set of upgrades? I think I'm well set all around except for one thing - I'm over the weight limit for my level. With everything organized and no coins, I believe it's 21-22. Keep in mind I'm dirt poor right now, but hey, I don't mind working on cash to pay off a decent upgrade. I'm going to guess the belt is too low of a haste for my level too.<br>
<br>
2) As stated, I have no 1hbs. I read the forum a lot, and notice that when people are talking about them, they never really clarify whether something is good only before epic fists, or after as well. Either way - any suggestions there? Is it not even worth worrying about right now? Keep in mind that the bulk of my time is spent soloing - or if I raid, I'm just a damage dealer, since an AAXPless monk seems low-demand for serious raid responsibility nowadays aside from CR. Also, just on a lark - I DO have a GSC and some other Goranga weapon banked - 8/17 or so ratio. Are those even worth using over epic fists, or no?<br>
<br>
3) A solo question - How much of a vicious-stab-in-the-eye is it to get from 57 to 60 solo? I'm in a small but cool guild that, alas, exps next to never. I've tried getting into pickup groups but to no avail - it seems like a guild only thing on Fennin Ro. So my potential options are soloing, which I've done for a long time (done for a long time anyway, just it's slowed up a ton now) or trying to move on to another guild. In other words - is it possible to pick up at least 10% or more a day soloing light blues / blues? Or am I looking at something more like 3% unless I two-box a shaman or start getting into CT or other groups somehow?<br>
<br>
Thanks in advance for the advice. I've been pretty happy with my progress so far, but for awhile now I've been hitting a wall on advancement, and want to know what I can do to handle it. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/unamsundeathmonkey.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Namsun DeathMonkey</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 860<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/2/02 2:25:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11696.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 57 Monk Needs Equip/other Advice</span><hr size=1> 1.  Not sure what the rotting gorilla helmet is, but if it's not better than Froggy crown or Shissar Scale Headband, then I'd buy one of those.  Also, if you're in a guild (which I'm assuming you are because you have a BoB), you can have them kill Lord Bob for a Turban.<br>
<br>
Not sure what you're earrings are either, but if they're not better than Black Sapphire Electrum (2 AC +35hp/mana) then go for a pair of those.  <br>
<br>
For the back slot pick up a Shimmering Terrorhide Cloak or a Spider Fur Cloak.  <br>
<br>
For arms pick up Hardened Grey Flesh Sleeves<br>
<br>
In regards to your haste, any haste is better than no haste.  If you stumble upon a lot of money somehow, rbg is the cheapest of the higher haste stuff.<br>
<br>
Also, I would invest in a Large Soiled Bag.  The bag makes a perfect banadage carrier <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
2.  Tstaff is better than most 1h combos that are attainable before you can kill higher end mobs.  I use a Tstaff too, and the only 1h weapons that would be better than my epic (epic does less dmg than Tstaff) that I can hope to attain atm Khashek's Katar and a Skybreaker.  Basically, stick with your Tstaff; it's good dmg and that's what we're about.<br>
<br>
3.  Soloing is super hard, especially now that they've nerfed xp.  If you can find 1 partner Nurga slaves used to be great xp solo/duo...but usually I just find a group.  If you're looking for easy places to get a pickup group, OS and Velks have always worked well.<br>
<br>
