Member of <A HREF=http://www.tkagiro.com>T`kagi Ro</A>, Fennin Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugaichin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>gaichin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk-in-Training</span><br>  Posts: 74<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(10/2/02 2:40:17 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=11696.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.bestweb.net/~buddha/pstgif.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: 57 Monk Needs Equip/other Advice</span><hr size=1> 1) I'd leave the dire wolf cloak on your back.  Its about the same as a terrorhide cloak, and much better than spider fur.  The only glaring, not-too-hard upgrade I see is the sleeves - grey flesh are the way to go.  Also might want to look into earrings with some hp, the solstice earring is nice for the price, at 5ac 55hp 5sv c/f/m (its nodrop, but you just buy 9 tradeable items and put them in a forge - its a no-fail combine)<br>
<br>
2) With a T-staff don't start worrying about 1hb's until your guild can do a place like NToV.  Would be a good idea to pick up a Stave of Shielding though, they're cheap (2-3k on Quellious) and proc Major Shielding: 75hp 18ac 14svmagic buff.  Also epic/SoS is a pretty nice dps combo for working h2h/1hb or for avoiding aggro on raids, etc.<br>
<br>
3) You have a fungi &amp; t-staff and are asking about soloing?!?  Holy crap 10% a day if you only have an hour to play.. You could reach 60 pretty fast, at 57 try to get LDC/SS in sol b, at 58/59 when they start to teal out, try roaming around velks grabbing any spider you see, or try the slaves in Nurga.  Personally I find Nurga boring, so I aa almost exclusively in velks.  At 60 each spider gives 1% aa.  Seb used to be a viable solo spot also, but a few weeks back somebody must have dosed Verant HQ with a huge amount of crack-smoke through the ventilation, because they felt that the changes to casters (i.e. Ice Comet) weren't powerful enough, and that no resist number should let us resist, even partially, any spell cast on us, so Seb is now out of the question :mad: <p><center>
